{{list to table|date=December 2016}} The '''Breakthrough of the Year''' is an annual award made by the [[American Association for the Advancement of Science|AAAS]] journal, ''[[Science (journal)|Science]]'', for the most significant development in scientific research. Originating in 1989 as the ''Molecule of the Year'', and inspired by ''Time''{{'s}} [[Time Magazine Person of the Year|Man of the Year]], it was renamed the Breakthrough of the Year in 1996. The Breakthrough of the Year is widely recognized as one of the highest distinctions in science.{{citation needed|date=December 2012}}
