{{other uses|EMPC (disambiguation)}}
'''Estimated maximum possible concentration''' (EMPC) is a term used in [[dioxin]] concentration determination for a concentration between [[limit of quantification]] and [[limit of detection]].<ref>Assessment of dioxin and dioxin-like compounds in mainstream smoke from selected US cigarette brands and reference cigarettes. C.L. Wilson, , J.A. Bodnar, B.G. Brown, W.T. Morgan, R.J. Potts and M.F. Borgerding, [[Food and Chemical Toxicology]], Volume 46, Issue 5, May 2008, Pages 1721–1733, {{doi|10.1016/j.fct.2008.01.009}}</ref>

