[[File:Swedish professor Vilhelm Lilljeborg.jpg|thumb|Vilhelm Lilljeborg]]
'''Wilhelm Lilljeborg''' (6 October 1816 – 24 July 1908) was a [[Sweden|Swedish]] [[zoology|zoologist]].<ref>{{cite book |author=David M. Damkaer |year=2002 |title=The copepodologist's cabinet: a biographical and bibliographical history |series=Volume 240 of Memoirs of the American Philosophical Society |publisher=[[American Philosophical Society]] |isbn=978-0-87169-240-5 |chapter=Transition |pages=272–274}}</ref> He is particularly known for his work on the [[Cladocera]] of Sweden, and on the [[Balaenoptera]]. Lilljeborg was a member of the [[Royal Swedish Academy of Sciences]] from 1861.

